{
  "texts": [
    "Both subjectively and objectively, the model was able to produce photographs of higher quality.",
    "Nearly three-fourths of those who provided comments on their suggested model concurred that it might produce visuals associated with sounds.",
    "The model demonstrated that it understood the association between sounds and visuals to some extent by responding to inputs of the same sound at various levels with varied scales of change.Without using interpretation, Wan et al. [80] sought to convert speech signals into visual cues.",
    "In order to improve generalisation on new classes, a voice encoder was created to represent the input speech signals as an embedding feature.",
    "It was then trained utilising teacher-student learning using an image encoder that had already been trained."
  ]
}